01,0.15434387,0.05543058,0.01938061,0.06863253,-0.02873258,-0.01099410,0.05626586,0.07752313,0.02577584,0.00176185,0.02136389,0.00511859,0.02268396,-0.02089706,0.03315316,0.01056853,0.05433684,-0.06810286,-0.02762848,0.05041391,-0.04509802,0.00588182,0.02765457,-0.01402934,0.04194748,-0.06452727,-0.07311736,0.00935109,0.02098563,-0.06194016,-0.01685810,0.00060410,-0.01194876,-0.01750476,-0.00697824,0.04814301,-0.04770165,0.01897072,0.05800765,-0.00601935,0.00177353,0.03317581,-0.01030711]',E'Embedded Database Support\n\nSimilarly to xref:data/sql.adoc#data.sql.datasource.embedded[the JDBC support], Spring Boot can automatically configure an embedded database for reactive usage.\nYou need not provide any connection URLs.\nYou need only include a build dependency to the embedded database that you want to use, as shown in the following example:\n\n[source,xml]\n----\n<dependency>\n	<groupId>io.r2dbc</groupId>\n	<artifactId>r2dbc-h2</artifactId>\n	<scope>runtime</scope>\n</dependency>\n----\n\n[NOTE]\n====\nIf you are using this feature in your tests, you may notice that the same database is reused by your whole test suite regardless of the number of application contexts that you use.\nIf you want to make sure that each context has a separate embedded database, you should set `spring.r2dbc.generate-unique-name` to `true`.\n====\n\n\n\n[[data.sql.r2dbc.using-database-client]]','{"source": "spring-boot", "version": "4.0", "language": "java", "title": "Sql.Adoc", "section_title": "sql.adoc", "url": "https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/blob/3.4.x/spring-boot-project/spring-boot-docs/src/docs/antora/modules/reference/pages/data/sql.adoc", "topics": "spring,boot,sql.adoc", "categories": "web,java,rest,enterprise"}');
